My initial reaction is much like a lot of others.  UGH!   After 2 years with my main character (after playing through 2 others to level 10 or so) I settled on my paladin.    Right now there would have to be a lot more than advertised for me to a) buy another new game b) have to buy new expansions as they come out c) start over.<br>
<br>
I do have some thoughts about what they could do to ease some of the burden and concerns:<br>
<br>
Using EQ as a basis....and extrapolating what might work in EQ2:<br>
<br>
What if at lvl 60, a warrior was FAR superior to a lvl 40 with full gear.   Give that lvl 60 a rusty sword, and leather and he will trounce people?   Perhaps Item decay will work because there will be a HUGE emphasis on skills and abilities over items.<br>
<br>
Perhaps there will be ranges of equipment.   As you go from a cloth shirt to plate mail to Valorium to Skyshrine to the breastplate of Vindication the decay factor goes from......1 day to 1 month to 1 year to never decays?   It is possible that as you get better and better armor it may not decay as rapidly and be far superior?<br>
<br>
I don't get the bank thing other than to make the world bigger and more realistic.   Of course, I am sceptical there, after all, we already know how annoying the boats are for the 50000000th time to make the world more realistic and expand the size of the world.<br>
<br>
EQ is the only MMORPG I have played.  It is/ has been a lot of fun and I have enjoyed it tremendously, which is why I still play.  <br>
<br>
I understand why they are making a new one to fix stuff, but this looks like a totally new everything.   I think if they took EQ, recoded the thing from the ground up, changed the fundemental issues with the game, stats, abilities, and reliance on equipment, they could breath new life into the game without having to throw everything out and starting over.    Of course, that is just my opinion.<br>
<br>
